The Zoning Resolution of the City of New York, effective as of December 15, 1961, and as subsequently amended, is further amended by changing the Zoning Map, Section No. 22d: 

1. changing from an M1-1 District to an R7A District property bounded by a line 100 feet southeasterly of 15th Avenue, 60th Street, a line 200 feet southeasterly of 15th Avenue, a line midway between 59th Street and 60th Street, a line 460 feet southeasterly of 15th Avenue, 60th Street, and the northerly boundary line of the Long Island Railroad right-of-way (Bay Ridge Division);  

2. establishing within the proposed R7A District a C2-4 District bounded by a line 100 feet southeasterly of 15th Avenue, 60th Street, a line 200 feet southeasterly of 15th Avenue, a line midway between 59th Street and 60th Street, a line 460 feet southeasterly of 15th Avenue, 60th Street, and the northerly boundary line of the Long Island Railroad right-of-way (Bay Ridge Division);  

as shown on a diagram (for illustrative purposes only) dated January 6, 2020, and subject to the conditions of CEQR Declaration E-556, Borough of Brooklyn, Community District 12.

Adopted.

